ders of the Chinese Communist Party mobilized an influential labor movement at the beginning of their revolution, and whose history later became a touchstone of "political correctness" in the People’s Republic of China. Once known as "China’s Little Moscow," Anyuan came over time to symbolize a distinctively Chinese revolutionary tradition. Yet the meanings of that tradition remain highly contested, as contemporary Chinese debate their revolutionary past in search of a new political future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAnyuan (Jiangxi Sheng, China : West)xPolitics and governmenty20th century. 0aAnyuan (Jiangxi Sheng, China : West)xSocial conditionsy20th century. 0aCoal minerszChinazAnyuan (Jiangxi Sheng : West)xHistoryy20th century. 0aCommunismzChinazAnyuan (Jiangxi Sheng : West)xHistoryy20th century. 0aLabor movementzChinazAnyuan (Jiangxi Sheng : West)xHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitical culturezChinazAnyuan (Jiangxi Sheng : West)xHistoryy20th century. 0aRevolutionsxSocial aspectszChinazAnyuan (Jiangxi Sheng : West)xHistoryy20th century. 0aSocial changezChinazAnyuan (Jiangxi Sheng : West)xHistoryy20th century. 0aWorking classzChinazAnyuan (Jiangxi Sheng : West)xHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh  a20th century china.  aancient china.  aasian history.  aasian politics.  achinese communism.  achinese communist party.  achinese culture.  achinese history.  achinese isolation.  achinese politics.  acommunist revolution.  aeasy to read.  aengaging.  ahistory of anyuan.  ahistory of communism.  ahome school history books.  ahow does communism work.  alearning from experts.  amao zedong.  anonfiction books.  apage turner.  apolitical science.  apolitics and economy.  aquarantine books.  ared scare.  